main event: Colonel Tootlian observed a large, round, metallic unidentified floating object in French Morocco on May 27, 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed at an estimated altitude of 10,000 feet above sea level.,The observation lasted between 20 to 30 minutes.,Colonel Tootlian has over 900 hours of flying time over water and noted the calm sea conditions during the sighting.,He referred to three other objects as sea markers to establish a line of sight with the UFO.,The description of the object was incomplete as per the record card comments.
